Bundle: #管理插件
http://github.com/gmarik/vundle
1、Setup Vundle:
git clone https://github.com/gmarik/vundle.git ~/.vim/bundle/vundle
2.Configure bundles:
#.vimrc:
3.Install configured bundles:
Launch vim . run :BundleInstall #BundleInstall! for update #BundleClean
When install YouCompleteMe...need to compile Vim from source.
Follow the link:
http://github.com/Valloric/YouCompleteMe
till hg clone https://code.google.com/p/vim
You should set http_proxy=127.0.0.1:8087 #use goagent
then hg clone https://code.google.com/p/vim --nosecur..
#factal
./configure --with-features=huge --enable-rubyi.. --enable-python.. --enable    -perlin.. --enable-gui=gnome2 --enable-cscope --prefix=/usr --with-python-co    nfig-dir=/usr/lib/python2.7/config...（Your python config)
sudo make install is prefertable..

